trick Doyle]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Warner Sunset\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix (soundtrack)|Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]''\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| {{Start date|df=yes|2007|7|10}}\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| 52:22\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Nicholas Hooper]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince (soundtrack)|Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]''\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| {{Start date|df=yes|2009|7|14}}\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| 62:40\n| [[New Line Records]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 1 (soundtrack)|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 1 (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]''\n| style=\"text-align:left\"|{{Start date|df=yes|2010|11|16}}\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| 73:38\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Alexandre Desplat]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[WaterTower Music]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2 (soundtrack)|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2 (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]''\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| {{Start date|df=yes|2011|7|12}}\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| 68:26\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them (soundtrack)|Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]''\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| {{Start date|df=yes|2016|11|18}}\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| 72:00\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[James Newton Howard]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| ''[[Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald (soundtrack)|Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]''\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| {{Start date|df=yes|2018|11|9}}\n| style=\"text-align:left\"| 77:17\n|-\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n{{hatnote|For more details on the reception of each film, see the \"Reception\" section on each film's article.}}\n\n===Box office performance===\n{{As of|2018}}, the first ten Wizarding World films have collectively grossed over $9.2 billion at the global box office, making it the [[List of highest-grossing film series#Highest-grossing franchises and film series|third-highest-grossing film franchise]] of all time behind the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] [[List of Marvel Cinematic Universe films|films]] and the ''[[Star Wars]]'' films. All ten films  emerged as commercial successes at the box office    with majority of the film's  grossing over $790 million, and all but ''Prisoner of Azkaban'' and ''Fantastic Beasts'' at some point ranked among the [[List of highest-grossing film series|ten highest-grossing films of all time]]. The [[Harry Potter (film series)|''Harry Potter'' films]] are the highest-grossing series based on a single property, earning over $7.7 billion at the box office;<ref name=\"AllTimeDomesticBOM\" /><ref name=\"HPTotalBOM\" /> ''Harry Potter'' has also generated at least $3.5 billion in home video revenue, taking total consumer spending on the films to over $11 billion.<ref name=\"TheNumbersHP\" /> ''Harry Potter'' also has a series average of over $1 billion per film when adjusted for inflation.<ref name=\"HPSeriesAverage\" />\n\n''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2'' grossed over $1.3 billion becoming the third-highest-grossing film of all time, the highest-grossing film in the Wizarding World franchise, and the [[2011 in film|highest-grossing film of 2011]].<ref name=\"BOM2011highest\" /> In the United States and Canada, it set a single-day and opening-weekend record, with $91,071,119 and $169,189,427.<ref name=\"DH2OpeningDay\" /><ref name=\"DH2OpeningWeekend\" /> In addition, the film set a worldwide opening-weekend record with $483,189,427.<ref name=\"DH2WorldwideDebut\" /><ref name=\"TheNumbersDH2\" /> ''Philosopher's Stone'' and ''Goblet of Fire'' were also the [[2001 in film|highest-grossing films of 2001]] and [[2005 in film|2005]];<ref name=\"BOM2001highest\" /><ref name=\"BOM2005highest\" /> while ''Chamber of Secrets'', ''Prisoner of Azkaban'', ''Order of the Phoenix'', and ''Half-Blood Prince'' were the [[2002 in film|second highest-grossing films of 2002]], [[2004 in film|2004]], [[2007 in film|2007]], and [[2009 in film|2009]].<ref name=\"BOM2002highest\" /><ref name=\"BOM2004highest\" /><ref name=\"BOM2007highest\" /><ref name=\"BOM2009highest\" /> ''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 1'' was the [[2010 in film|third-highest-grossing film of 2010]], (behind ''[[Toy Story 3]]'' and ''[[Alice in Wonderland (2010 film)|Alice in Wonderland]])'',<ref name=\"BOM2010highest\" /> ''[[Fantastic Beasts]]'' was the eighth  highest-grossing film of 2016.<ref name=\"BOM2016highest\" /> ''[[Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald|Crimes of Grindelwald]]'' was the tenth highest grossing film of 2018.\n\n<!-- UPDATE ACCESSDATE IN REF WHEN UPDATING A ROW -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center\" width=99%\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Film\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Release date\n! colspan=\"3\" |Box office gross\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" text=\"wrap\" class=unsortable | All-time ranking\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Budget\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" class=unsortable | {{nowrap|{{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}}}\n|-\n! U.S. & Canada\n! Other territories\n! Worldwide\n! class=unsortable | [[List of highest-grossing films in the United States and Canada#Not adjusted for inflation|U.S. & Canada]]\n! class=unsortable | [[List of highest-grossing films|Worldwide]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"9\" style=\"background-color:#ccccff;\" | ''Harry Potter'' films\n|-\n| ''Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone''\n| {{start date|df=yes|2001|11|16}}\n| $318,087,620\n| $659,999,992\n| $978,087,613\n| 65\n| 40\n| $125 million\n| <ref name=\"HP1BOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=harrypotter.htm |title=Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone (2