=\"9\" style=\"background-color:#ccccff;\" | ''Fantastic Beasts'' films\n|-\n| ''Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them''\n| {{start date|df=yes|2016|11|18}}\n| $234,037,575\n| $580,000,000\n| $814,037,575\n| 140\n| 76\n| $180 million\n| <ref name=\"FB1BOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=fantasticbeasts.htm |title=Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them (2016) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=31 January 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170624132551/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=fantasticbeasts.htm |archivedate=24 June 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald''\n| {{start date|df=yes|2018|11|16}}\n| $159,555,901\n| $494,100,000\n| $654,655,901\n| 321\n| 127\n| $200 million\n| <ref name=\"FB2BOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=wbevent2018.htm |title=Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald (2018) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=31 January 2019 }}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Total\n! $2,786,941,008\n! $6,425,969,105\n! $9,213,910,121\n! 3\n! 3\n! ${{formatnum:{{#expr:125000000+100000000+130000000+150000000+150000000+250000000+125000000+125000000+180000000+200000000}}}}\n! <ref name=\"AllTimeDomesticBOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/?view=Franchise&sort=sumgross&order=DESC&p=.htm |title=Franchise Index |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=31 January 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140524020558/http://boxofficemojo.com/franchises/?view=Franchise&sort=sumgross&order=DESC&p=.htm |archivedate=24 May 2014 }}</ref><br /><ref name=\"TotalBOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=jkrowling.htm |title=J.K. Rowling's Wizarding World Movies at the Box Office |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=31 January 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630205456/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=jkrowling.htm |archivedate=30 June 2017 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Critical and public response===\nAll the films have been a success commercially and the majority a success critically, making the franchise one of the major Hollywood \"tent-poles\" akin to ''[[James Bond in film|James Bond]]'', ''[[Star Wars]]'', ''[[Indiana Jones (franchise)|Indiana Jones]]'', ''[[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|Lord of the Rings]]'' and ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean (film series)|Pirates of the Caribbean]]''. The ''Harry Potter'' series is noted by audiences for growing visually [[dark fantasy|darker]] and more mature as each film was released.<ref name=\"ColumbusDark\" /><ref name=\"TimeDarker\" /><ref name=\"ReutersDark\" /><ref name=\"DarkMoody\" />\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center\" width=99%\n|-\n! '''Film'''\n! '''[[Rotten Tomatoes]]'''\n! '''[[Metacritic]]'''\n! '''[[CinemaScore]]'''\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"background-color:#ccccff;\" | ''Harry Potter'' films\n|-\n| ''Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone''\n| 81% (198 reviews)<ref name=\"RThp1\">{{cite web|title=Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone (2001) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/harry_potter_and_the_sorcerers_stone/ |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=14 November 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203134925/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/harry_potter_and_the_sorcerers_stone/ |archivedate=3 December 2013 }}</ref>\n| 64 (36 reviews)<ref name=\"MChp1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/video/titles/harrypotterandthesorcerersstone |title=Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone (2001): Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=14 November 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090711202402/http://www.metacritic.com/video/titles/harrypotterandthesorcerersstone |archivedate=11 July 2009 }}</ref>\n| A<ref name=\"HPcs\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemascore.com/ |title=Cinemascore |publisher=[[CinemaScore]] |accessdate=21 February 2