19 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709200351/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/harry_potter_and_the_deathly_hallows_part_2_2011/ |archivedate=9 July 2016 }}</ref>\n| 87 (41 reviews)<ref name=\"MChp8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/harry-potter-and-the-deathly-hallows-part-2 |title=Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2 (2011): Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=14 November 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718094558/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/harry-potter-and-the-deathly-hallows-part-2 |archivedate=18 July 2011 }}</ref>\n| A<ref name=\"HPcs\" />\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" style=\"background-color:#ccccff;\" | ''Fantastic Beasts'' films\n|-\n| ''Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them''\n| 74% (333 reviews)<ref name=\"RTfb1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/fantastic_beasts_and_where_to_find_them |title=Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them (2016) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=November 1, 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606012241/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/fantastic_beasts_and_where_to_find_them |archivedate=6 June 2017 }}</ref>\n| 66 (50 reviews)<ref name=\"MCfb1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/fantastic-beasts-and-where-to-find-them |title=Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=14 November 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128234709/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/fantastic-beasts-and-where-to-find-them |archivedate=28 November 2016 }}</ref>\n| A<ref name=\"HPcs\" />\n|-\n| ''Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald''\n| 36% (314 reviews)<ref name=\"RTfb2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/fantastic_beasts_the_crimes_of_grindelwald/|title=Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald (2016) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=November 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| 52 (48 reviews)<ref name=\"MCfb2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/fantastic-beasts-the-crimes-of-grindelwald |title=Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n| B+<ref name=\"HPcs\" />\n|}\n\n===Accolades===\n\n====Academy Awards====\nSeven of the ten films were nominated for a total of 14 [[Academy Awards]]. ''Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them'' won for [[Academy Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]] in [[89th Academy Awards|2017]], becoming the first film in the Wizarding World to win an Academy Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/02/27/oscars-2017-fantastic-beasts-and-where-to-find-them-wins-first-oscar-for-harry-potter-franchise |title=Oscars 2017: Fantastic Beasts Wins First Academy Award for Harry Potter Franchise |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=26 February 2017 |website=[[IGN]] |language=en-US |accessdate=27 February 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227023421/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/02/27/oscars-2017-fantastic-beasts-and-where-to-find-them-wins-first-oscar-for-harry-potter-franchise |archivedate=27 February 2017 }}</ref> Before the win in 2017, the franchise was the most-[[wikt:snub|snubbed]], top-grossing franchise of all time at the Academy Awards, with 12 nominations and zero wins.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/297110/thanks-academy-oscars-make-harry-potter-most-snubbed-franchise-of-all-time |title=Thanks, Academy: Oscars Make Harry Potter Most-Snubbed Franchise of All-Time |last=Ryan |first=Joal |date=27 February 2012 |work=[[E! Online]] |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303222120/http://www.eonline.com/news/297110/thanks-academy-oscars-make-harry-potter-most-snubbed-franchise-of-all-time |archivedate=3 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\" width=99%\n! align=\"center\" width=\"16%\" | Film\n! align=\"center\" width=\"14%\" | [[Academy Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"14%\" | [[Academy Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"14%\" | [[Academy Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"14%\" | [[Academy Award for Best Visual Effects|Best Visual Effects]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"14%\" | [[Academy Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"14%\" | [[Academy Award for Best Makeup and Hairstyling|Best Makeup]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Philosopher's Stone''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2002\">{{cite news|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2002 |title=The 74th Academy Awards (2002) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=19 November 2011 |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS) |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109213431/http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2002 |archivedate=9 November 2014 }}</ref>\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2002\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2002\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Prisoner of Azkaban''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2005\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2005 |title=The 77th Academy Awards (2005) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=25 January 2015 |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS) |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101230853/http://oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2005 |archivedate=1 January 2016 }}</ref>\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2005\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Goblet of Fire''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2006\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2006 |title=The 78th Academy Awards (2006) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=20 November 2011 |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS) |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109220946/http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2006 |archivedate=9 November 2014 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Half-Blood Prince''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2010\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2010 |title=The 82nd Academy Awards (2010) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=10 November 2011 |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS) |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141130021624/http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2010 |archivedate=30 November 2014 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 1''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2011\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2011 |title=The 83rd Academy Awards (2011) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=11 November 2011 |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS) |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5yxj8yoHk?url=http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/83/nominees.html |archivedate=26 May 2011 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2011\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2012\">{{cite news|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2012 |title=The 84th Academy Awards (2012) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=26 April 2012 |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS) |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141015232303/http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2012 |archivedate=15 October 2014 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2012\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2012\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Fantastic Beasts''\n| {{won}}<ref name=\"Oscars2017\">{{cite news|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2017 |title=The 89th Academy Awards (2017) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=26 February 2017 |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] (AMPAS) |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227001154/http://oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2017 |archivedate=27 February 2017 }}</ref>\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"Oscars2017\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n|}\n\n====British Academy Film Awards====\nThe franchise has earned a total of 32 nominations at the [[British Academy Film Awards]] presented at the annual [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTAs]], winning three. At the [[64th British Academy Film Awards]] in February 2011, Rowling, producers Heyman and Barron, along with directors Yates, Newell and Cuar\u00f3n collected the [[BAFTA Outstanding British Contribution to Cinema Award|Michael Balcon Award for Outstanding British Contribution to Cinema]] in honour of the ''Harry Potter'' film series.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-12353795 |title=Harry Potter franchise to get Outstanding BAFTA award |work=[[BBC Online]] |date=3 February 2011 |accessdate=3 February 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110204111609/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-12353795 |archivedate=4 February 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bafta.org/awards/film/outstanding-british-contribution-to-cinema-the-harry-potter-films,1631,BA.html |title=Outstanding British Contribution to Cinema in 2011 \u2013 The Harry Potter films |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |date=3 February 2011 |accessdate=3 February 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110206001409/http://www.bafta.org/awards/film/outstanding-british-contribution-to-cinema-the-harry-potter-films%2C1631%2CBA.html |archivedate=6 February 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The ''Harry Potter'' series was also recognised by the [[Britannia Awards|BAFTA Los Angeles Britannia Awards]], with Yates winning the Britannia Award for Artistic Excellence in Directing for his four ''Harry Potter'' films.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://losangeles.broadwayworld.com/article/BAFTA-Honors-John-Lasseter-and-David-Yates-1130-20110628 |title=BAFTA Honors John Lasseter and David Yates 11/30 |publisher=[[Broadway Worldwide]] (Los Angeles) |date=28 June 2011 |accessdate=28 June 2011 |quote=The worldwide success of Mr. Lasseter for Walt Disney and Pixar Animation Studios and Mr. Yates' contribution to the final four parts of the 'Harry Potter' franchise makes them global wizards in their own right, and are delighted to honor these remarkable filmmakers with this year's Britannia Award. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120120084528/http://losangeles.broadwayworld.com/article/BAFTA-Honors-John-Lasseter-and-David-Yates-1130-20110628 |archivedate=20 January 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/awards/2011/06/john-lasseter-and-david-yates-set-to-be-honored-by-bafta-los-angeles-.html |title=John Lasseter and David Yates set to be honored by BAFTA Los Angeles |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=28 June 2011 |accessdate=28 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110703082314/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/awards/2011/06/john-lasseter-and-david-yates-set-to-be-honored-by-bafta-los-angeles-.html |archivedate=3 July 2011 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\" width=99%\n! align=\"center\" width=\"16%\" | Film\n! align=\"center\" width=\"12%\" | [[BAFTA Award for Best British Film|Best British Film]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"12%\" | [[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role|Best Supporting Actor]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"12%\" | [[BAFTA Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"12%\" | [[BAFTA Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"12%\" | [[BAFTA Award for Best Makeup and Hair|Best Makeup & Hair]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"12%\" | [[BAFTA Award for Best Sound|Best Sound]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"12%\" | [[BAFTA Award for Best Special Visual Effects|Best Visual Effects]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Philosopher's Stone''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2002\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2002/film? |title=Film in 2002 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141104151316/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2002/film |archivedate=4 November 2014 }}</ref>\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2002\" /><br />([[Robbie Coltrane]])\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2002\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2002\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2002\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2002\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2002\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Chamber of Secrets''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2003\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2003/film? |title=Film in 2003 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504182458/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2003/film |archivedate=4 May 2016 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2003\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2003\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Prisoner of Azkaban''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2005\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2005/film? |title=Film in 2005 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160528145230/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2005/film/ |archivedate=28 May 2016 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2005\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2005\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2005\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Goblet of Fire''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{won}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2006\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2006/film? |title=Film in 2006 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305144619/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2006/film |archivedate=5 March 2016 }}</ref>\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2006\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2006\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Order of the Phoenix''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2008\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2008/film? |title=Film in 2008 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417073548/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2008/film/ |archivedate=17 April 2017 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2008\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Half-Blood Prince''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2010\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2010/film? |title=Film in 2010 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504184904/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2010/film |archivedate=4 May 2016 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2010\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 1''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2011\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2011/film? |title=Film in 2011 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504200733/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2011/film |archivedate=4 May 2016 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2011\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2012\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2012/film? |title=Film in 2012 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305073916/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2012/film |archivedate=5 March 2016 }}</ref>\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2012\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2012\" />\n| {{won}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2012\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Fantastic Beasts''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2017\">{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2017/film? |title=Film in 2017 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=5 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170615121754/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2017/film |archivedate=15 June 2017 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2017\" />\n| {{won}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2017\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2017\" />\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2017\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''The Crimes of Grindelwald''\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2019\">{{cite web |url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2019/film? |title=Film in 2019 |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) |accessdate=30 April 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190430052833/http://awards.bafta.org/award/2019/film |archivedate=30 April 2019 }}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"BAFTA2019\" />\n|-\n|}\n\n====Grammy Awards====\nThe franchise has received a total of six [[Grammy Award]] nominations, all for films in the ''Harry Potter'' series.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\" width=70%\n! align=\"center\" width=\"16%\" | Film\n! align=\"center\" width=\"27%\" | [[Grammy Award for Best Score Soundtrack for Visual Media|Best Score Soundtrack for Visual Media]]\n! align=\"center\" width=\"27%\" | [[Grammy Award for Best Instrumental Composition|Best Instrumental Composition]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Philosopher's Stone''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"GrammysWilliams\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/john-williams |title=John Williams |accessdate=5 July 2017 |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"GrammysWilliams\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Chamber of Secrets''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"GrammysWilliams\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Prisoner of Azkaban''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"GrammysWilliams\" />\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Half-Blood Prince''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"GrammysHooper\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/nicholas-hooper |title=Nicholas Hooper |accessdate=5 July 2017 |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Deathly Hallows \u2013 Part 2''\n| {{nom}}<ref name=\"GrammysDesplat\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/alexandre-desplat |title=Alexandre Desplat |accessdate=5 July 2017 |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n|}\n\n====Laurence Olivier Awards====\n''Harry Potter and the Cursed Child'' garnered eleven [[Laurence Olivier Award]]s nominations at the [[2017 Laurence Olivier Awards|2017 ceremony]], tying the record set in [[2008 Laurence Olivier Awards|2008]] by ''[[Hairspray (musical)|Hairspray]]'', and won a record-breaking nine: [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best New Play|Best New Play]], [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Director|Best Director]], [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] (Jamie Parker), [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]] (Noma Dumezweni), [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role|Best Actor in a Supporting Role]] (Anthony Boyle), [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]], [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Set Design|Best Set Design]], [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Sound Design|Best Sound Design]], and [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Lighting Design|Best Lighting Design]]. The London production was also nominated for [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Theatre Choreographer|Best Theatre Choreographer]] and [[Laurence Olivier Award for Outstanding Achievement in Music|Outstanding Achievement in Music]].<ref name=\"LOAnoms\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/harry-potter-cursed-child-breaks-olivier-awards-record-11-nominations/ |title='Harry Potter and the Cursed Child' Breaks Olivier Awards Record With 11 Nominations |work=[[TheWrap]] |last=Geier |first=Thom |date=6 March 2017 |accessdate=12 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505050617/http://www.thewrap.com/harry-potter-cursed-child-breaks-olivier-awards-record-11-nominations/ |archivedate=5 May 2017 }}</ref><ref name=\"LOAwins\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2017/olivier-awards-2017-harry-potter-and-the-cursed-child-wins-record-nine-prizes/ |title=Olivier Awards 2017: Harry Potter and the Cursed Child wins record nine prizes |work=[[The Stage]] |last=Bano |first=Tim |date=9 April 2017 |accessdate=12 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415040142/https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2017/olivier-awards-2017-harry-potter-and-the-cursed-child-wins-record-nine-prizes/ |archivedate=15 April 2017 }}</ref>\n\n====Tony Awards====\n''Harry Potter and the Cursed Child'' received ten nominations at the [[72nd Tony Awards]], winning six awards: [[Tony Award for Best Play|Best Play]], [[Tony Award for Best Scenic Design in a Play|Best Scenic Design in a Play]], [[Tony Award for Best Costume Design in a Play|Best Costume Design in a Play]], [[Tony Award for Best Lighting Design in a Play|Best Lighting Design in a Play]], [[Tony Award for Best Sound Design|Best Sound Design of a Play]], and [[Tony Award for Best Direction of a Play|Best Direction of a Play]]. The play was also nominated for [[Tony Award for Best Actor in a Play|Best Performance by a Leading Actor in a Play]] (Parker), [[Tony Award for Best Featured Actor in a Play|Best Performance by a Featured Actor in a Play]] (Boyle), [[Tony Award for Best Featured Actress in a Play|Best Performance by a Featured Actress in a Play]] (Dumezweni), and [[Tony Award for Best Choreography|Best Choreography]].<ref name=\"TonyNoms\">{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/legit/awards/2018-tony-awards-nominations-list-broadway-1202792611/ |title=Tony Nominations 2018: 'Mean Girls,' 'SpongeBob' Score Big (Complete List) |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |last=Cox |first=Gordon |date=1 May 2018 |accessdate=2 May 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180502001406/http://variety.com/2018/legit/awards/2018-tony-awards-nominations-list-broadway-1202792611/ |archivedate=2 May 2018 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"TonyWins\">{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/legit/awards/tony-award-winners-2018-complete-list-1202839347/ |title=Tony Award Winners 2018: The Complete List |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |last=Nyren |first=Erin |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180611043413/https://variety.com/2018/legit/awards/tony-award-winners-2018-complete-list-1202839347/ |archivedate=11 June 2018 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Outside media==\n\n===Pottermore===\n{{Main|Pottermore}}\nIn June 2011, Rowling launched a website announcing an upcoming project called [[Pottermore]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory?id=13858046 |title=J.K. Rowling Has Mysterious New Potter Website |publisher=[[ABC News]] |agency=[[Associated Press]] |date=16 June 2011 |accessdate=16 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110618134045/http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory?id=13858046 |archivedate=18 June 2011 }}</ref> where all future ''Harry Potter'' projects, and all electronic downloads, would be concentrated.<ref>{{cite news|title=JK Rowling launches Pottermore Website |first=Anita |last=Singh |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/harry-potter/8579560/JK-Rowling-launches-Pottermore-website.html |accessdate=4 July 2011 |location=London |date=16 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711235447/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/harry-potter/8579560/JK-Rowling-launches-Pottermore-website.html |archivedate=11 July 2011 }}</ref> Pottermore opened to the general public on 14 April 2012.<ref name=\"waiting\">{{cite web|url=http://insider.pottermore.com/2012/03/waiting-for-pottermore.html |title=Waiting for Pottermore? |publisher=[[Pottermore]] |date=8 March 2012 |accessdate=9 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310102525/http://insider.pottermore.com/2012/03/waiting-for-pottermore.html |archivedate=10 March 2012 }}</ref> Pottermore allows users to be sorted, be chosen by their wand and play various minigames. The main purpose of the website was to allow the user to journey through the story with access to content not revealed by J.{{nbsp}}K. Rowling previously, with over 18,000 words of information on characters, places and objects in the ''Harry Potter'' universe.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://newsfeed.time.com/2011/06/23/pottermore-secrets-revealed-j-k-rowlings-new-site-is-e-book-meets-interactive-world |title='Pottermore' Secrets Revealed: J.K. Rowling's New Site is E-Book Meets Interactive World |first=Sonia van |last=Gilder Cooke |date=23 June 2011 |magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=6 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120829110641/http://newsfeed.time.com/2011/06/23/pottermore-secrets-revealed-j-k-rowlings-new-site-is-e-book-meets-interactive-world/ |archivedate=29 August 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pottermore website launched by JK Rowling as 'give-back' to fans |first=Alison |last=Flood |work=[[The Guardian]] |location=London |url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/jun/23/pottermore-website-jk-rowling-harry-potter |accessdate=4 July 2011 |date=23 June 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715090227/http://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/jun/23/pottermore-website-jk-rowling-harry-potter |archivedate=15 July 2014 }}</ref> In September 2015, the website launched a newly designed site containing news, features and articles plus previously unreleased writing by Rowling and removed some features including the interactive Moment illustrations, House Cup and Sorting ceremony.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pottermore |url=https://www.pottermore.com/news/Welcome-to-the-new-Pottermore |publisher=[[Pottermore]] |accessdate=8 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926135910/https://www.pottermore.com/news/Welcome-to-the-new-Pottermore |archivedate=26 September 2015 }}</ref> A newly designed Sorting Ceremony was subsequently launched on 28 January 2016 in which users could reclaim their old house or be re-sorted.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/harry-potter-what-hogwarts-house-am-i-in-2016-1 |title=You can finally reclaim your old Hogwarts house and wand on Pottermore \u2014 here's how |work=[[Business Insider]] |date=28 January 2016 |accessdate=4 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017202805/http://www.businessinsider.com/harry-potter-what-hogwarts-house-am-i-in-2016-1 |archivedate=17 October 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Theme park attractions===\n{{Main|The Wizarding World of Harry Potter}}\n[[The Wizarding World of Harry Potter]] are a group of themed areas at [[Universal Parks & Resorts]] based on the ''Harry Potter'' media franchise, adapting elements from the film series and original novels by Rowling. The areas were designed by [[Universal Creative]] under an exclusive licence with [[Warner Bros. Entertainment]].<ref name=bbc070531>{{cite news|title=Harry Potter theme park planned |newspaper=[[BBC News]] |date=31 May 2007 |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/6706939.stm?lsm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512225739/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/6706939.stm?lsm |archivedate=12 May 2014 }}</ref><ref name=guardian070531>{{cite news|accessdate=19 May 2010 |title=Harry Potter theme park to open in Florida |last=Sturcke |first=James |newspaper=The Guardian |date=31 May 2007 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2007/may/31/film.harrypotter |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130831080623/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2007/may/31/film.harrypotter |archivedate=31 August 2013 }}</ref><ref name=usatoday070531>{{cite news|title=Harry Potter theme park swoops to Fla. |newspaper=[[USA Today]] |date=31 May 2007 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/2007-05-31-harry-potter-park_n.htm |accessdate=19 May 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011180722/http://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/2007-05-31-harry-potter-park_n.htm |archivedate=11 October 2008 }}</ref><ref name=stpetersburg070601>{{cite news |title=A whole new magic kingdom |last=Albright |first=Mark |newspaper=[[The St. Petersburg Times]] |date=1 June 2007 |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=rMUnAAAAIBAJ&sjid=g3QDAAAAIBAJ&dq=harry-potter%20theme-park%20disney&pg=2741%2C6435 |accessdate=19 May 2010}}</ref> It opened on 18 June 2010 as an expansion to the [[Islands of Adventure]] theme park at [[Universal Orlando Resort]] in Orlando, Florida,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/travel/attractions/wizarding-world-of-harry-potter/os-universal-harry-potter-staying-pow20100617,0,1970029.story |title=Big day is here: Universal hopes Harry Potter's magic will last|first=Jason|last=Garcia|date=17 June 2010|accessdate=19 June 2010|newspaper=[[Orlando Sentinel]]}}</ref> and on 8 July 2014 at the [[Universal Studios Florida]] theme park.\n\nOn 15 July 2014, The Wizarding World of Harry Potter opened at the [[Universal Studios Japan]] theme park in Osaka, Japan. It includes the village of [[Hogsmeade]], the [[Harry Potter and the Forbidden Journey]] ride, and the [[Flight of the Hippogriff]] roller coaster.<ref name=orlando20140418>{{cite news|last=Bevil |first=Dewayne |date=18 April 2014 |title=Universal Studios Japan: Wizarding World of Harry Potter to open July 15 |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/travel/attractions/theme-park-rangers-blog/os-universal-studios-japan-harry-potter-20140418-post.html |newspaper=[[Orlando Sentinel]] |accessdate=12 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912073410/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/travel/attractions/theme-park-rangers-blog/os-universal-studios-japan-harry-potter-20140418-post.html |archivedate=12 September 2014 }}</ref><ref name=cnn20140716>{{cite news|last=Cripps |first=Karla |date=16 July 2014 |title=Universal Studios Japan's 'Wizarding World of Harry Potter' opens |url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/07/16/travel/universal-studios-japan-harry-potter/ |publisher=[[CNN]] |accessdate=12 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912075407/http://www.cnn.com/2014/07/16/travel/universal-studios-japan-harry-potter/ |archivedate=12 September 2014 }}</ref> On 7 April 2016, The Wizarding World of Harry Potter opened at the [[Universal Studios Hollywood]] theme park near Los Angeles, California.<ref name=nytimes20140409>{{cite news|last=Barnes |first=Brooks |date=8 April 2014 |title=A Makeover at Universal Studios Hollywood Aims at Disney |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/09/business/media/a-makeover-of-universal-studios-hollywood-aims-to-catch-up-to-disney.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |location=[[Universal City, California]] |accessdate=12 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912083943/http://www.nytimes.